# Product Development Rules — Trivense vs Competitors

Goal: faster, simpler, more modern, better for India/travelers/power users — NOT a clone.

## Competitors (equal weight — check all three)

| App | Focus | Play Store |
|-----|-------|------------|
| **Tricount** | Group split/settle, free, travel-focused, multi-currency, offline | [link](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.tribab.tricount.android) |
| **Splitwise** | Group split/settle, freemium, export, web, recurring bills, premium limits | [link](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.Splitwise.SplitwiseMobile) |
| **Wallet** | Budget/expense tracker, bank sync, subscriptions, multicurrency, reports | [link](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.droid4you.application.wallet) |

Listing assets for all competitors live under `store-assets/competitors/{tricount,splitwise,wallet}/play/`.

## Out of scope (do not build or suggest)

**Photos / receipts** — no receipt attach, receipt gallery, or photo upload on expenses. Do not propose parity with Tricount photo sharing or Splitwise Pro OCR/receipt storage.

**AI features** — no OCR, auto-categorization via ML, voice/NL expense entry, AI summaries, anomaly detection, or other AI/ML-powered features. Prefer simple rules, smart defaults, and clear UX instead.

If Tricount, Splitwise, or Wallet have photos/AI-like capabilities, **do not copy them**. Compete on split/settle, boards, analytics, export, sync, and pricing — not photos or AI.

**Bank account linking** — Wallet's core is automatic bank sync. Do not chase full bank-aggregator parity unless explicitly scoped; Trivense focuses on manual/offline-first group splitting.

## Before every change

1. Does **Tricount** have this? How do they solve it?
2. Does **Splitwise** have this? How do they solve it?
3. Does **Wallet** have this? How do they solve it?
4. Can we simplify, speed up, or automate without AI?
5. Retention, reviews, premium potential?
6. Never implement just because it exists — and never implement out-of-scope items above.

## Feature removal

Never remove without checking **Tricount, Splitwise, and Wallet**. If any of them has it → do not remove; improve, premium-gate, optionalize, or redesign. Remove only if UX harm, confusion, duplication, or zero usage.

## Mandatory analysis format

For feature discussions provide **all three**:

- **Tricount** — has/how/strengths/weaknesses
- **Splitwise** — has/how/strengths/weaknesses
- **Wallet** — has/how/strengths/weaknesses
- **Our app** — current/gaps/UX wins
- **Recommendation** — KEEP | IMPROVE | REDESIGN | ADD | REMOVE

## UX priorities

Less taps/typing, smart defaults (non-AI), offline-first, fast load, one-handed use, clear empty states & onboarding, dark mode, accessibility.

## Automation (allowed, non-AI)

Settlement math, split calculations, budget alerts, recurring reminders (rule-based), export formatting, sync — no machine learning required.

## Premium classification

Every feature: Free | Premium | Enterprise — with WHY. Benchmark against Tricount (free), Splitwise Pro limits, and Wallet subscription tiers.

## Engineering

Clean architecture, offline-first, optimistic UI, background sync, Supabase RLS, indexing, performance.

## Decision framework

If a request makes us worse than **Tricount, Splitwise, or Wallet** → stop, explain, suggest better. If any competitor solves it better → explain theirs, propose improved version. If we lack parity with any of the three on a relevant feature → flag immediately.

## Response footer (feature/product work)

End with **Competitive Assessment**: parity % vs Tricount, Splitwise, and Wallet (each), UX improvement, performance, complexity, user value, should implement, plus 2–5 competitive improvements.
